Outstanding evening at The Press Hotel. It is housed in building that was the former home of the Portland Press. Everywhere you look the design and aesthetic reflect that. There are old typewriters, printing press pieces, letters used for typesetting, books and more. How inspirational it would be to stay here as a writer! Not to mention how great the cocktails are at @inkwelllounge and how delicious the food is at @unionportland.

Straddling the Spree. 
From the Oberbaum Bridge, you can see how the river flows through the city Center of Berlin.

Who wouldnâ€™t want to take a gardening class in here? The Red Barns at The Kelly Way Gardens at @woodstock.inn #historichotels

Ask any local in #StSimmonsIsland and they will tell you that Wild Georgia Shrimp are the best shrimp youâ€™ll ever taste. The official state tree of Georgia is the Live Oak. These beauties are on located on the grounds of the Jekyll Island off the coast of Georgia. In the late 1800s Jekyll Island was an exclusive hunting club for prestigious families like Rockefeller, Morgan, Vanderbilt, Pulitzer, and Baker. Take a tour the island to see their vacation homes or stay at the Historic Jekyll Island Club Hotel. 
The trees are covered in spanish moss, a flowering plant. 
Fun Fact: It is not actually a moss at all. It is a bromeliad which is the same family as a pineapple !

The @stsimonslighthouse is one of only five surviving lighthouses in Georgia. It is the 2nd lighthouse to stand in this spot. The first one was built in 1810 by James Gould, a plantation owner. It is built from 'tabby' which is a mixture of oyster shells, lime, sand and water. Unfortunately the original lighthouse was destroyed and the one you see now was built in 1872. This 104ft tower has 129 steps. Have you ever climbed to the top of a lighthouse? #goldenisles #kingandprinceresort

Originally built in 1877 the Roanoke Marshes Lighthouse once aided mariners in the Croatan Sound. It was decommissioned in 1955. During an attempt to move the Lighthouse to private property, the building was destroyed. A recreation now stands at the end of of a pier at the Manteo Waterfront Marina. This cottage style lighthouse served as both a residence and beacon of light for those arriving by boat.

This is one of many coastal lighthouse that can be found on the Outer Banks of North Carolina.
